<div class="howto_section">
  <h2>Getting Started</h2>

  <h3>Tips & Instructions</h3>

  <p>Here are some features available to you: </p>

  <strong><p>Creating New User </p></strong>
  <ul>
    <li>Go to the User panel and click the “New User” button.</li>
    <li>Enter the user’s first name, last name and email address to register them for the mobility  health apps.</li>
    <li>Select a study that the user should belong to.</li>
    <li>Users can be edited and deleted under the User panel.</li>
  </ul>
    
  <strong><p>Viewing Users</p></strong>
  <ul>
    <li>Under the User panel, for each individual user, there are columns that indicate the time the user last uploaded data on the mobility health apps and the studies that they belong to.</li>
    <li>Click on the “View” button for an individual user to get a visual view of data and download data from different data streams in csv format.</li>
    <li>csv format files are available in PAM, Mobility, ohmage, and Mobility daily summary data.</li>
    <li>The Mobility daily summary is shown on the Calendar with options for a monthly or a yearly view.</li>
    <li>When a specific date on the calendar is clicked, a comment input box will appear where you can enter any annotations.</li>
  </ul>

  <strong><p>Viewing Studies</p></strong>
  <ul>
    <li>Click on the Study panel.</li>
    <li>The name of the data stream and the survey that belong to the study are shown.</li>
  </ul>

  <strong><p>Viewing Surveys</p></strong>
  <ul>
    <li>Click on the Survey panel.</li>
    <li>The survey that is used in the study is shown.</li>
  </ul>

  <strong><p>We’re here to help</p></strong>
  <p>We want researchers to get the most out of SDL Admin Dashboard. If you have any questions or feedback, please contact us. We’ll get back to you as soon as possible. 
  </p>

